docs.abstract: A fireball producer is giving him a comeback chance while also trying to revive the tired celebrity news genre. It’s Mr. Bush’s first TV job since the infamous “Access Hollywood” tape.
docs.snippet: A fireball producer is giving him a comeback chance while also trying to revive the tired celebrity news genre. It’s Mr. Bush’s first TV job since the infamous “Access Hollywood” tape.
docs.lead_paragraph: BURBANK, Calif. — The television producer Lisa Gregorisch-Dempsey is known for her terrifying candor. The nameplate on her desk at Telepictures, where she has run the celebrity news show “Extra” for 19 years, sums up her style: “I’ll be nicer if you’ll be smarter.” But even her longtime lieutenants were a bit startled by the way she laid it on the line for Billy Bush when she interviewed him for a job last year.

headline.main: Billy Bush Is Ready for a Return to TV. Will Viewers Welcome Him Back?
headline.print_headline: Billy Bush Gets a Second Chance

docs.lead_paragraph: Stocks fell sharply on Wall Street on Friday after President Trump responded to China’s threat of new tariffs on American imports with an angry volley of tweets, helping to push the market to its fourth-straight weekly loss.

headline.main: S&P, Dow and Nasdaq Slide After China Tariff Threat and Trump Twitter Response
headline.print_headline: Trump Swings at China, and Markets Duck
